    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Harmony -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as a role-based interactive learning portal. The core architectural choice is a dynamic content filtering system based on user roles (e.g., Cashier, Floor Staff, Supervisor). This structure was chosen because the source report details highly differentiated responsibilities. A one-size-fits-all presentation would be inefficient and overwhelming. The user flow is: 1. Select Role -> 2. Content Adapts -> 3. Explore Sections. Navigation is handled by a top bar linking to key thematic areas: 'Inicio' (Home), 'Marco Normativo' (Regulatory Framework), 'Procedimientos Clave' (Key Procedures), and 'Señales de Alerta' (Red Flags). This design prioritizes usability and targeted learning, ensuring each employee receives precisely the information they need to perform their duties effectively, thus enhancing comprehension and compliance. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Differentiated employee responsibilities. -> Goal: Personalize learning. -> Viz/Method: Interactive role selector (HTML/JS buttons). -> Interaction: Click to filter all page content. -> Justification: Directly addresses the core challenge of the source material, making it relevant and digestible for each user.
        - Report Info: Key entities supervising the sector (MINCETUR, SBS, etc.). -> Goal: Clarify complex regulatory structure. -> Viz/Method: Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas). -> Interaction: Static visualization for quick comprehension. -> Justification: A visual chart is more intuitive for understanding hierarchical or multi-agency relationships than a text list.
        - Report Info: The process of identifying and reporting suspicious operations. -> Goal: Illustrate the operational workflow. -> Viz/Method: Interactive flowchart (HTML/CSS/JS). -> Interaction: Clicking a step reveals role-specific details. -> Justification: Makes the abstract process tangible and shows how individual roles connect within the larger compliance framework.
        - Report Info: Monetary threshold for RO (US$ 2,500). -> Goal: Highlight a critical data point. -> Viz/Method: Prominent info card (HTML/CSS). -> Interaction: Static, high-visibility element. -> Justification: Ensures the most critical operational number is impossible to miss.
        - Report Info: Lists of red flags. -> Goal: Make warning signs memorable. -> Viz/Method: Accordion-style interactive list (HTML/JS). -> Interaction: Click to expand/collapse categories. -> Justification: Breaks down a long list into manageable, categorized chunks, improving readability and retention over a static list.
        - Library/Method: Chart.js for the bar chart. All other visuals and interactions are built with HTML, Tailwind CSS, and vanilla JavaScript.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
